  "prompt": "Is 291 a good score in gre?",
  "response": "A GRE score of 291 is considered below average. The GRE is scored on a scale of 130 to 170 for both the Verbal Reasoning and Quantitative Reasoning sections, with a combined total score range of 260 to 340. A score of 291 suggests performance somewhat lower than the median score, which is usually around 300.\n\nHowever, whether a score is considered \"good\" can depend on the specific requirements of the programs to which you are applying. Some programs might have higher score expectations, particularly in competitive fields or prestigious institutions, while others might emphasize other application components, such as your academic record, letters of recommendation, or personal statement.\n\nIf your score falls short of the typical range required by your programs of interest, you might consider retaking the exam, especially if you believe you can improve with additional study or preparation.",
